defaulturning an innovation into market opportunity can be difficult for a number of reasons. For example, customers are not always keen to be the first mover when it comes to buying a new and relatively unknown product. Another issue can be that sales people nee
defaultd to learn how to sell new products or services, and this can take time. These challenges in turning innovation into market opportunities are a particular issue given that manufacturers expect to use innovation to develop new markets. 
