default 
defaultWhile 
defaultR&amp;D expenditure is not a perfect measure of innovation
default, 
defaultit is a valuable metric and 
defaultit is 
defaultmeasured by a range of international comparator countries.
default BERD is a key component of this. 
default&#xa0;
defaultA7.
default 
defaultThe SME R&amp;D tax c
defaultredit indicator is important as R&amp;D expenditure is concentrated in large businesses, and smaller companies face the most acute barriers to innovation
default.
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;defaultProgress has been made default&#xa0;defaultA8.
default 
defaultTo date we have seen
default 
defaultprogress against both of these measures. BERD reached pre
default-recession levels after strong growth in 2011 and the number of SMEs claiming the R&amp;D tax credit increased by 49% between 2008/09 and 2011/12.
default&#xa0;
defaultA9.
default 
defaultRecent improvements to the SME R&amp;D tax credit scheme and the relative stability of its provision through the tax
default regime will have played a part in the significant increase in the number of companies using the scheme in the past three years.
